This program implements the Banker’s Algorithm used in operating systems for deadlock avoidance.


It takes:


Allocation matrix


Max matrix


Available resources




Then calculates:


Need = Max − Allocation




Logic:


Check if a process’s need ≤ available resources


If yes → execute it, release its resources


Add it to safe sequence


Repeat for all processes




If all processes execute → Safe State


If not → Unsafe State (possible deadlock)


👉 In short:
It checks whether the system can execute all processes safely without causing deadlock and gives a safe sequence.


