This program demonstrates memory allocation techniques in Operating Systems:

First Fit
Best Fit
Worst Fit
🔹 Logic:
Memory blocks and process sizes are given.
Each algorithm allocates processes differently:
First Fit
→ Allocates the first block that is large enough.
Best Fit
→ Allocates the smallest suitable block (minimizes wastage).
Worst Fit
→ Allocates the largest block (leaves big remaining space).
After allocation, block size is reduced.

👉 In short:
This code compares three memory allocation strategies and shows how processes are assigned to memory blocks differently.

