This program demonstrates process creation using fork() in Operating Systems.

🔹 Concept:
Uses fork system call
🔹 Logic:
fork() creates a child process
After fork:
pid == 0 → Child process executes
pid > 0 → Parent process executes
Child prints message and terminates using exit()
Parent continues execution

👉 In short:
This code shows how a parent process creates a child process and both run independently.

